title: CFIUS review of 1995 Magnequench sale (Committee on Foreign Investment in the United States)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any and all available documents, records, or communications between January 1, 1995, and today, relating to the CFIUS review of the 1995 purchase of Magnequench by the Sextant Group, San Huan New Material, and the China National Non-Ferrous Metals Import and Export Corporation.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Aaron Jerome

title: Touhy Park Tent Encampment CPD Materials

communications.subject: Illinois Freedom of Information Act. Request: Touhy Park Tent Encampment CPD Materials
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

All interdepartmental materials pertaining to the Touhy Park homeless encampment, including memorandums, background papers, meeting minutes, or presentation materials. 

If your office has questions about this request, please feel free to direct them to the address associated with this request.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Alexandra Gelzin

communications.subject: Illinois Freedom of Information Act. Request: Touhy Park Tent Encampment
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

First, all email exchanges between 24th District Commander Joseph Brennan and Touhy Park supervisor Misty Mitchell regarding the homeless encampment at Touhy Park and enforcement of the new Touhy Park curfew since January 1, 2023.

Second, all email exchanges between 24th District Commander Joseph Brennan and the office of Alderwoman Maria Hadden regarding the homeless encampment at Touhy Park and enforcement of the new Touhy Park curfew since January 1, 2023.

If your office has questions about this request, please feel free to direct them to the address associated with this request.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Alexandra Gelzin
